## How to iterate (the short version)

1. Justin describes a change in chat with Claude
2. Claude edits `MoveMeToEU.jsx` and delivers via downloadable file, **and includes the ready-to-paste PowerShell workflow block in the chat response with the commit message filled in** (see "Standard update workflow")
3. Justin runs the PowerShell block (OneDrive path, Move-Item, git push)
4. Render auto-deploys
5. Justin verifies at movemeto.eu

No local branching, no PRs, no code review. The project is intentionally low-ceremony.

**File integrity verification after every major edit:** Confirm braces balance and the file ends with `export default function MoveMeToEU() {...}` closing brace at the last line. The sanity-check script:

```javascript
const code = fs.readFileSync('MoveMeToEU.jsx', 'utf8');
const count = (c) => (code.match(new RegExp('\\' + c, 'g')) || []).length;
console.log('lines:', code.split('\n').length);
console.log('braces:', count('{'), '/', count('}'));
console.log('brackets:', count('['), '/', count(']'));
```

